SIMPLE: tough
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tough
<hw>Tough</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Tougher</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Toughest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>tough</ets>, AS.
<ets>t⟦omac⟧h</ets>, akin to D. <ets>taai</ets>, LG. <ets>taa</ets>,
<ets>tage</ets>, <ets>tau</ets>, OHG. <ets>z⟦amac⟧hi</ets>, G.
<ets>z⟦aum⟧he</ets>, and also to AS. ge<ets>tenge</ets> near to, close
to, oppressive, OS. bi<ets>tengi</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having
the quality of flexibility without brittleness; yielding to force
without breaking; capable of resisting great strain; <as>as, the
ligaments of animals are remarkably <ex>tough</ex></as>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Tough</xex> roots and stubs. ⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not easily broken; able to endure hardship; firm;
strong; -- of objects and people; <as>as, <ex>tough</ex>
sinews</as>.</def> <rj><au>Cowper.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A body made of brass, the crone demands, . . . ⟦br⟧
<qex>Tough</qex> to the last, and with no toil to tire.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The basis of his character was caution combined with
<qex>tough</qex> tenacity of purpose.</q> <rj><qau>J. A.
Symonds.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Not easily separated; viscous; clammy; tenacious;
<as>as, <ex>tough</ex> phlegm</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Stiff; rigid; not flexible; stubborn; <as>as, a
<ex>tough</ex> bow</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So <qex>tough</qex> a frame she could not bend.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>Severe; violent; <as>as, a <ex>tough</ex>
storm</as>.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧ A <xex>tough</xex>
debate. ⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Difficult to do, perform, or accomplish; <as>as, a
<ex>tough</ex> job</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>Prone to aggressive or violent behavior; rowdyish;
-- of people, or groups; <as>as, a <ex>tough</ex> neighborhood; a
<ex>tough</ex> character</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To make it tough</b></col>, <cd>to make it a matter of
difficulty; to make it a hard matter.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>tough</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: tough
<hw>tough</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person who is
tough{7}; a ruffian; a thug; <as>as, a cluster of neighborhood
<ex>toughs</ex> hanging out on the corner</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tough-cake</ent>⟦br⟧
